
HYDERABAD, JAN. 1. The Andhra Pradesh Government has decided to comply with the Tamil Nadu request for release of water into the Telugu Ganga to supplement drinking water supplies for Chennai.
However, the release will be possible only after a month, in view of the repair works taken up on the canal beyond Kandaleru reservoir. The works relate to removal of silt, landslips and boulders from the canal- bed which block the flow.
According to a senior official in the Irrigation Department, the tenders for these works costing Rs. 46 lakhs, will be finalised on January 17. After selection of the bidder the works may not be delayed.Efforts were also on to provide irrigation to the planned ayacut in parts of Rayalseema region under the project.
